other_tests.findings: The gallbladder is markedly distended containing multiple shadowing gallstones, one of which is lodged within the gallbladder neck. No gallbladder wall thickening, edema, or pericholecystic fluid. Sonographic Murphy's sign was negative. No intra or extrahepatic biliary duct dilatation is present with the common bile duct measuring 4 mm.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Since the prior study, no new hepatic lesions were identified. The previously noted cyst within segment 6 of the liver was not imaged on the current exam.
